2)WRITE A QUERY THAT GIVES THE NAMES OF BOTH THE SALESPERSON AND THE CUSTOMER FOR EACH ORDER ALONG WITH THE ORDER NUMBER.

kd4_rahul_83497@localhost>SELECT ORDERS.Onum, CUSTOMERS.cname, SALESPEOPLE.sname FROM ORDERS JOIN CUSTOMERS ON ORDERS.cnum = CUSTOMERS.cnum JOIN SALESPEOPLE ON ORDERS.snum = SALESPEOPLE.snum order by 1;
+------+----------+---------+
| Onum | cname    | sname   |
+------+----------+---------+
| 3001 | Cisneros | Rifkin  |
| 3002 | Pereira  | Motika  |
| 3003 | Hoffaman | Peel    |
| 3005 | Liu      | Serres  |
| 3006 | Cisneros | Rifkin  |
| 3007 | Grass    | Serres  |
| 3008 | Clemens  | Peel    |
| 3009 | Giovanni | Axelrod |
| 3010 | Grass    | Serres  |
| 3011 | Clemens  | Peel    |
+------+----------+---------+
10 rows in set (0.00 sec)


