3)WRITE A QUERY THAT PRODUCES ALL CUSTOMERS SERVICED BY SALESPEOPLE WITH A COMMISSION ABOVE 128. OUTPUT THE CUSTOMER'S NAME, THE SALESPERSON'S NAME, AND THE SALESPERSON'S RATE OF COMMISSION.

kd4_rahul_83497@localhost>select Cname,Sname,Comm from CUSTOMERS,SALESPEOPLE where CUSTOMERS.Snum=SALESPEOPLE.Snum and SALESPEOPLE.Comm>0.12;
+----------+--------+------+
| Cname    | Sname  | Comm |
+----------+--------+------+
| Liu      | Serres | 0.13 |
| Grass    | Serres | 0.13 |
| Cisneros | Rifkin | 0.15 |
+----------+--------+------+
3 rows in set (0.00 sec)


==========================================================================================================================================================================================================
4)WRITE A QUERY THAT CALCULATES THE AMOUNT OF THE SALESPERSON'S COMMISSION ON EACH ORDER BY A CUSTOMER WITH A RATING ABOVE 100.

kd4_rahul_83497@localhost>SELECT Onum, Cname, Sname, Amt * comm AS commission_amount FROM ORDERS JOIN CUSTOMERS ON ORDERS.cnum = CUSTOMERS.cnum JOIN SALESPEOPLE ON ORDERS.snum = SALESPEOPLE.snum WHERE CUSTOMERS.rating > 100;
+------+----------+---------+-------------------+
| Onum | Cname    | Sname   | commission_amount |
+------+----------+---------+-------------------+
| 3010 | Grass    | Serres  |            170.29 |
| 3007 | Grass    | Serres  |              9.85 |
| 3005 | Liu      | Serres  |            670.86 |
| 3006 | Cisneros | Rifkin  |            164.72 |
| 3001 | Cisneros | Rifkin  |              2.80 |
| 3009 | Giovanni | Axelrod |            171.32 |
+------+----------+---------+-------------------+
6 rows in set (0.00 sec)


